name: Grinnell Glacier
summary: An incredible out-and-back hike to the most visited glacier in all of Glacier National Park.

name: Avalanche Lake
summary: A well-traveled, easy and open hike with scenery for the record books; one of Glacier's best!

name: Hidden Lake Overlook
summary: A shorter, out-and-back hike from the Logan Pass Visitor Center to the Hidden Lake Overlook.

name: Highline to The Loop
summary: One of the most iconic hikes in Glacier National Park, with easy access off of Logan Pass.
cond_details: Dry, Mostly Dry: Trail was mostly dry

name: Iceberg Lake
summary: An out-and-back hike to Iceberg Lake with ample opportunity to see a variety of Glacier's megafauna!
cond_details: No longer posted on nps for recent bear frequenting

name: St. Mary / Virginia Falls
summary: A highly-visited hike to a pair of powerful, rushing falls that make for a nice out-and-back route.

name: Siyeh Pass Route
summary: Work your way past alpine flower meadows, breathtaking views, fantastic mountains, and a glacier.

name: Cracker Lake
summary: Camp beneath one of the largest rock faces on the continent.

name: Gunsight Pass
summary: A long hike from the Jackson Glacier Overlook, over Gunsight Pass, to the Lake McDonald Lodge.
cond_details: Snowy - A few snowfields (~3) approaching Gunsight Pass from Gunsight Lake, but most should be bypassable or crossed with trekking poles.

name: Many Glacier Loop
summary: A mountainous 60-mile loop around Many Glacier, Goat Haunt, and Lake McDonald Areas.

name: Ptarmigan Tunnel Route
summary: A hike up to a unique 250-foot tunnel through a sheer, rock wall with incredible views on each side.

name: Grinnell Lake
summary: Head out from the Many Glacier Hotel along the southern lake shores and creeks leading to Grinnell.

name: Boulder Pass Loop
summary: An epic alpine adventure with some of the finest scenery Glacier National Park has to offer.

name: Mount Brown Lookout
summary: A journey along a crazy steep trail with absolutely no reprieve leads to a well worthwhile viewpoint

name: Carthew - Alderson Traverse
summary: One of most beautiful hikes ever; fir forests, alpine meadows, wildflowers, peaks, turquoise lakes, snow, roaring creek.

name: Bullhead Lake
summary: A moderate day-hike to Bullhead Lake along Swiftcurrent Creek, past the beautiful Redrock Falls.

name: Baring Falls
summary: A short route down to Baring Falls below Sunrift Gorge, gets you up close and personal to the spray.

name: Blakiston Falls
summary: A forested hike that follows Blakiston Creek on its way to to Blakiston Falls.

name: Goat Lake
summary: A switchback climb with exposure leads to a small sub-alpine lake with stellar mountain views.

name: Jewel Basin Loop
summary: A splendid romp through some of Montana's finest scenery.

name: Coal Nyack Loop
summary: A large loop tour of the Middle Fork region of Glacier National Park.

name: Park Creek
summary: A deep-woods hike into the seldom-visited Middle Fork region of Glacier National Park.

name: Florence Falls from Gunsight Pass Trailhead
summary: A quiet hike out to Florence Falls from the Jackson Glacier Overlook on the GTSR.

name: Hidden Lake
summary: An alpine trail across flowering alpine meadows backdropped with peaks to a beautiful lake.

name: Grinnell Glacier Overlook
summary: This short, steep trail leads you to the top of the Garden Wall overlooking the Grinnell Glacier.
cond_details: Dry, Mostly Dry: Trail was mostly dry

name: Grinnell Glacier Trail
summary: One of Glaciers most famous trail, this moderate trail leads you right up to Grinnell Glacier itself

name: Swiftcurrent Pass
summary: Trail travels from moose frequented lakes among rocky summits, past waterfalls to alpine meadows.

name: Apgar Lookout
summary: Travel through a burn area that gives you a great view of Lake McDonald.

name: Trail of the Cedars
summary: One of Glacier's two wheelchair accessible trails, it takes you through the parks only cedar forest.

name: Siyeh Pass Trail
summary: A breathtaking trail that takes you from dense forest to uninterrupted views from the summit.
cond_details: Mostly Dry - Dry from siyeh bend to pass but a three snow crossings down to sun highway if you do thru hike.

name: Stoney Indian Pass
summary: Follow an incredible chain of lakes up past waterfalls and alpine lakes and ponds, then back down.

name: Red Gap Pass
summary: A wonderfully varied trail through a forest, past a lake, and up rocky slopes to a red rock pass.

name: Sperry Glacier
summary: Great alpine trail up through rock ledges, past waterfalls and blue lakes onto a glacier.

name: Helen Lake Trail
summary: A fantastic trail along a lake, up through forests, and alpine meadows to a picturesque alpine lake.

name: Medicine Grizzly Trail
summary: A hike through pleasant forests and meadows to a perfect lake tucked beneath epic mountains.

name: Two Medicine Pass
summary: A strenuous yet rewarding trail, it affords some uncommon views into the southern end of the park.

name: CDT: Many Glacier to Goat Haunt (MT Sec. 30)
summary: This section of the CDT features some of Glacier's best, from incredible lakes to high alpine.

name: Swiftcurrent Lookout
summary: Panoramic views of breathtaking mountains escort you up a switchback trail to an incredible lookout.

name: Lee Ridge Trail
summary: From lodgepole forest to an epic ridge with breathtaking, 360-degree views in a remote area.

name: Ellen Wilson Trail
summary: This short, alpine trail leads to one of the greatest campgrounds in Glacier National Park.

name: Waterton Valley
summary: From the large Waterton Lake, through the trees, then up to the sublime, wide open alpine.

name: Bear Mountain Point
summary: Incredible views of the Mokowanis and Belly River drainages and surrounding, epic peaks.

name: Ousel Peak Trail #331
summary: Climb up a rugged, steep ridgeline to reach amazing views from Ousel Peak.

name: Beardance Trail #76
summary: A good mix of rocks and roots. Either direction is great.

name: Great Divide Trail - Section A (Canada/USA Border to Coleman)
summary: Canadian Rockies at their best, wild and beautiful, along the Continental Divide.

name: Whitefish Trail-Haskill Section
summary: A Whitefish trail in Haskill Basin.

name: Blacktail to Lakeside Trail
summary: A steady climb or descent with nice views along the way.

name: Gunsight Pass Trail
summary: A wooded trail that climbs through a pass before dropping into Lake McDonald.

name: Rainbow Falls
summary: A secluded trail through woods and meadow along a river to a series of falls over uplifted rock.

name: Morrell Falls National Recreation Trail #30
summary: A very popular hike to a stunning waterfall!

name: Porcupine Lookout
summary: From the dense forest below to the high alpine perch, this trail explodes with a crescendo of views.

name: Granite Park Campground Trail
summary: Incredible alpine hike from trees, past campsites to open expanses with incredible peaks all around.

name: Mokowanis Lake Trail
summary: A lazy trail through the woods that takes you to a perfect lake.

name: Hole in the Wall Campground Connector
summary: A superb alpine setting of wildflowers surrounded by cathedral walls covered in waterfalls.

name: Sue Lake Overlook
summary: A short trail with panoramic views to a sublime overlook of Sue Lake and the drainage behind it.

name: Alpine Trail (South)
summary: A high traverse along the ridge with alpine peaks and endless views.

name: Lake Isabel Trail
summary: Stunning peaks and pristine tarns.

name: Great Divide Trail - Barnaby Ridge Alternate Route
summary: GDT Alternate Route along an open, high and scenic ridge.

name: Surprise Pass
summary: It's called Surprise Pass because you'll hardly notice, then, SURPRISE!  You're over it!

name: Belly Ranger Station Trail
summary: A wonderful trail featuring big open meadows with views along a river with some forest mixed in.

name: Martha's Basin Trail
summary: A short, easy side hike to view Beaver and Buffalo Woman lakes.

name: Great Divide Trail - Mt Rowe/Sage Pass Alternate Route
summary: GDT Alternate Route on a high ridge on the Continental Divide. Awesome views!

name: St. Mary Corral Cutoff - overgrown and for administrative use only.
Crypt Lake Trail
summary: This trail requires a ferry to the trailhead, features stunning views of a lake, and involves crawling through a tunnel.

name: Highline Trail
summary: A popular, flat, long traverse with stunning views, wildflowers, and frequent wildlife sightings.

name: Notch Trail
summary: Savor some great views along this switchbacking trail.

name: Piegan Pass Trail
summary: An incredibly varied epic of a trail from lakes to forest to alpine, past waterfalls and back down.

name: Iceberg Lake Trail
summary: Traverse the alpine with epic views to a beautiful lake with icebergs tucked under cathedral walls.

name: Boulder Pass Trail
summary: A taste of East, West, and Central Glacier National Park.

name: Ptarmigan Trail
summary: A varied forest and alpine route that travels through a man-made tunnel through a rock wall.

name: Florence Falls
summary: This short spur trail off of the Gunsight Pass trail takes you to a tall, wonderful cascade.

name: Bowman Lake Trail
summary: A generally flat, seven mile hike to a nice camp on Bowman Lake.

name: Upper McDonald Creek
summary: A short, level trail that meanders through the forest along the edge of picturesque McDonald Creek.

name: Mt. Aeneas Trail #717
summary: Amazing views of the Flathead Valley and Jewel Basin.

name: Bond Creek Trail #21
summary: A scenic route with a waterfall and high alpine lakes.

name: Huckleberry Lookout Trail
summary: As straightforward as the name implies; get your hiking legs warm and berry-picking hands ready.

name: South Boundary
summary: Traverse the south boundary of Glacier along the banks of the beautiful Middle Fork Flathead River.

name: Ahern Pass Overlook Trail
summary: A spur trail takes you along alpine terrain to an incredible overlook of Helen Lake at Ahern Pass.

name: Jackson Glacier Trail
summary: A steep trail leading to an epic traverse below Jackson Glacier with fantastic views.

name: Foys to Blacktail Trail
summary: An isolated adventure that links the crowded Kalispell scene to the seldom traveled ski hill.

name: Rising Sun
summary: A level, meandering trail along the shores of St. Mary Lake with plenty of views and skipping rocks.

name: Triple Divide
summary: A strenuous Montana trail, with steep inclines, and rewarding views.

name: Avalanche Trail
summary: This route among the cool cedar and hemlock forest is a great place for peace and solitude.

name: Carthew - Alderson Trail
summary: A remote trail through gorgeous mountain scenery; meadows, wildflowers, peaks, turquoise lakes, fir forests, & creeks.

name: Apikuni Falls
summary: This short, steep trail leads to a beautiful waterfall tucked beneath the rocky cliffs.

name: Harrison Lake
summary: A forested path leads to the shores of a beautiful green colored lake nestled below wooded mountains

name: Otokomi Lake
summary: A trail along a bubbling creek to a beautiful lake nestled in a basin made of stunning, red rocks.

name: North Shore Lake Josephine Trail
summary: This amazing hike along the north shore of Lake Josephine gives you fantastic views.

name: Swiftcurrent Lake Trail
summary: A gentle loop around Swiftcurrent Lake with wonderful views and a chance to see many animals.
cond_details: Dry - Mother bear and cub spotted on the trail.

name: Quartz Lake Loop
summary: A hike that starts at a beautiful lake and travels through varied forests visiting three other lakes.

name: Flattop Mountain
summary: Start in the forest, through an old burn, then up onto wonderful, open alpine meadows with views.
cond_details: Dry - plenty dry and huckleberries were perfectly ripe!

name: Holland Falls National Recreation Trail #416
summary: This trail rises gently along a lake to a spectacular waterfall.

name: Rocky Point Trail
summary: On this trail, you'll get fantastic views of Lake McDonald and see the amazing impacts of wildfires.

name: Bertha Lake Trail
summary: A forested climb past Lower and Upper Bertha Falls, followed by a short descent to Bertha Lake, surrounded by peaks.

name: Red Rock Canyon Loop
summary: An easily accessed path along an exquisite section of the Red Rock Canyon.

name: Numa Ridge
summary: A trail up a wooded ridge that breaks up to incredible views of an emerald lake and jagged peaks.

name: Cosley Lake Cutoff
summary: A wonderful mixed forest featuring views of stunning peaks and a beautiful Cascade.

name: Big Salmon to Upper Holand Lake
summary: Last full day on the trail.

name: Scalplock Lookout
summary: Primarily a trail through trees to get to an exceptional vantage in the southern section of Glacier.

name: Stanton Lake Trail #146
summary: This is a popular trail with great views next to Stanton Lake.

name: Grinnell Lake Trail
summary: A hike through dense forest along a creek to turquoise Grinnell Lake in a towering glacial cirque.

name: Siyeh Bend Trail
summary: This well-marked, charmingly wooded trail feels like you have escaped into the wild.

name: Mt Brown Trail
summary: One of Glacier's more rigorous trails, the view from the top rewards those who make the climb.

name: Nyack Creek Trail
summary: One of the deepest backcountry experiences you can have while still on-trail in Glacier.

name: Glacier Creek Trail #690
summary: Needs Summary

name: Bitterroot Trail
summary: One of the only trails in the park that allows you to roam with buffalo.

name: McDonald Creek Cutoff
summary: A hike through the old growth forest of the McDonald Creek drainage to the shores of the creek.

name: Camas Creek Trail
summary: A nice combination of forested trail with large meadows backdropped by epic mountains.

name: St. Mary Lake Trail
summary: A varied trail featuring waterfalls, big mountains, a gorgeous lake and a mix of old and burn forest

name: Lakeshore Trail
summary: A well-maintained, forested trail along Upper Waterton Lake.

name: Great Divide Trail - Waterton Detour Alternate Route
summary: GDT Alternate Route to detour around Waterton closed area. Visits prairie, hills, forested slopes and small lakes.

name: Hidden Meadow
summary: A short trail through some trees brings you to a tranquil meadow with a lovely pond.
cond_details: Dry - Two white swans swimming.  Trail is clear and uncrowded.

name: Red Eagle
summary: Wonderful views abound as you hike through a burned area to a lake tucked beneath massive peaks.

name: Phillips Trail #373
summary: A steep climb leading to some contouring trail and a short descent to the road.

name: Echo Broken Leg Trail #544
summary: A pretty easy singletrack trail with rewarding views!

name: West Lakes Trail
summary: A trail up and over a steep ridge leads to a wooded valley with a chain of lakes.

name: Loneman Lookout
summary: Views abound to the top of a mountain with a staffed lookout in a quiet, remote corner of Glacier.

name: Goat Lake Trail
summary: A challenging climb with exposure leading to a small sub-alpine lake with mountain views.

name: Gable Pass
summary: This trail is steep up and steep down, but passes an incredible alpine section with epic views.

name: Kishenehn Trail
summary: A remote trail on the old Inside North Fork Road parallels a beautiful river through varied forest.

name: Otatso Creek Trail
summary: A pleasant route from Slide Lake out along a creek to the park boundary.

name: South Shore Lake Josephine Trail
summary: A pleasant trail through trees and along the south shore of the beautiful Lake Josephine.

name: Kishenehn Creek Trail
summary: A remote stretch of trail to the Canadian border through trees that's remarkably well-maintained.

name: NF Belly River
summary: A little route finding through meadows takes you to around a ridge to a remote river drainage.

name: Great Divide Trail - Mt Rowe/Sage Pass Access Alternate Route
summary: GDT Alternate Route that climbs Mt. Rowe to get to a scenic high ridge and the Mt Rowe/Sage Pass Alternate Route.

name: Belly River Trail
summary: A combination of lodgepole pines, aspens, and epic meadows with fantastic views.

name: Snyder Lake Trail
summary: A trip through a narrow valley with a wet forest and lake tucked beneath tall, rocky cliffs.

name: The Loop Trail
summary: The trail takes you from burn area through subalpine fir forest to alpine meadows with premium views

name: Lincoln Lake
summary: A long, wooded route that's short on views until it ends with a beautiful lake and large waterfall.

name: Johns Lake
summary: A hike through tall cedars from a whitewater creek to a pocket lake.

name: Apgar Bike Trail
summary: A convenient and peaceful hiking and biking path that connects the entrance to Apgar Village.

name: Summit Lake Trail
summary: A beautiful switchback climb through fir forests to Summit Lake, a sub-alpine lake.

name: CDT: Goat Haunt to Waterton Townsite (MT Sec. 30C - Lakeshore Trail)
summary: A wonderful trail that follows the western edge of the magnificent Waterton Lake to the town.

name: Cut Bank Pass
summary: A bruiser of a trail leading from beautiful high alpine to forested valleys below.

name: Logging Lake Trail
summary: A wooded trail to quiet lakes nestled beneath wooded ridges.

name: Park Creek Trail
summary: Explore Park Creek in the Middle Fork region of Glacier National Park.

name: Ptarmigan Trail - Altyn/Henkel Connector
summary: Rarely used trail traditionally used as the main trail from Many Glacier Hotel to Ptarmigan Tunnel.

name: Nyack Crossing Trail
summary: Ford the Middle Fork Flathead River to join South Boundary and Nyack Creek Trail.

name: Swiftcurrent Pass - Altyn/Henkel Connector
summary: Rarely used trail traditionally used as the main trail from Many Glacier Hotel to Swiftcurrent Pass.

name: Josephine Walk
summary: A raised trail along the head of a beautiful lake with great views and a chance to see moose.

summary: Needs Adoption
cond_details: Dry - Hiked this on 7/26. Access to the trailhead is easy via a semi-paved road that is well marked on the highway. Trail is a gentle slope up to the lake, then double back to the main trail for the hike to the top. the grades on the switchbacks are also pretty gentle, so it never feels like you're gaining 2000 feet of elevation. views get better and better as you climb. Views from the top are fantastic. Once past the lake we only saw six other people on the trail. Definitely recommend this hike.

name: Blue Lake Loop
summary: This route is filled with beautiful mountains and scenery that reminds me of the Sierras.
cond_details: Dry - Hiked up to Minam Lake on 8/19. Road to Two Pan campground is in good shape. Trail is very dry and dusty and the Granite Gulch fire is burning one ridge over beyond the lake. This limited visibility and was an annoyance at times, but the late afternoon sun through the smoke proved incredible for the lighting. Although the trailhead parking was full of cars, we saw only five other hikers all day. Great views around the lakes and the meadows are incredible. Decent dry fly fishing for brook trout as well. A great introductory hike for those interested in what the Eagle Cap holds.
